Class ProjectRegistry

java.lang.Object
BTO_Management_System.ProjectRegistry
public class ProjectRegistry extends Object
A registry class that holds and manages all BTO projects in the system. It provides static methods to access, add, remove, find, filter, and sort projects.

    • getAllProjects

      public static List<BTOProject> getAllProjects()
      Retrieves an unmodifiable list containing all the BTO projects in the registry. This returns a new list, so modifications to the returned list will not affect the registry.
      Returns:
      A new List of all BTOProject objects.

    • findProject

      public static BTOProject findProject(String name)
      Finds a BTO project in the registry by its name. The search is case-insensitive.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the project to search for.
      Returns:
      The BTOProject object if found, otherwise null.

    • filterProjects

      public static List<BTOProject> filterProjects(List<BTOProject> projects, List<String> locations, List<FlatType> flatTypes)
      Filters a list of BTO projects based on specified locations and flat types. If the locations or flatTypes list is empty, no filtering is applied for that criteria.
      Parameters:
      projects - The list of BTOProject objects to filter.
      locations - A list of neighborhood names to filter by. Projects in these locations will be included. An empty list means no filtering by location.
      flatTypes - A list of FlatType to filter by. Projects offering at least one of these flat types will be included. An empty list means no filtering by flat type.
      Returns:
      A new List containing the BTO projects that match the filter criteria.

    • sortProjects

      public static List<BTOProject> sortProjects(List<BTOProject> projects, String sortBy)
      Sorts a list of BTO projects based on the specified criteria. Supported sorting criteria are "ALPHABETICAL" (by project name), "LOCATION", and "FLAT_TYPE" (by the first flat type offered). The sorting is case-sensitive for string comparisons. If an invalid or null sortBy criteria is provided, the list is sorted alphabetically by project name.
      Parameters:
      projects - The list of BTOProject objects to sort.
      sortBy - The sorting criteria as a string ("ALPHABETICAL", "LOCATION", "FLAT_TYPE").
      Returns:
      The sorted List of BTO projects. The original list is modified in place.
